<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I&#39;m using the following snippet to hide org-PROPERTIES inside deft: </p> <p><code> (setq deft-strip-summary-regexp (concat &quot;\\(&quot; &quot;[\n\t]&quot; ;; blank &quot;\\|^#\\+[[:alpha:]_]+:.*$&quot; ;; org-mode metadata &quot;\\|^:PROPERTIES:\n\\(.+\n\\)+:END:\n&quot; &quot;\\)&quot;)) </code></p> <p>Now the problem is I usually add tags with every start of a new roam node, this causes an ugly view: </p> <p><a href="https://i.imgur.com/DJa8qvd.png">https://i.imgur.com/DJa8qvd.png</a></p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Mahdi_Amel"> /u/Mahdi_Amel </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wgrq3e/roamdeft_how_to_hide_tags_line_from_deft/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wgrq3e/roamdeft_how_to_hide_tags_line_from_deft/">[comments]</a></span>